&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Urology Nurse Practitioner – Band 6 – Urology – 23.5 hours per week – Permanent &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Could you help West Suffolk Hospital to deliver the best quality and safest care to our local community?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a highly motivated nurse to work as part of a small team, to be responsible for assisting in the provision of, and co-ordinating the care for patients who have urological conditions. This includes the delivery of holistic evidence-based care to patients with urology and oncology needs. The provision of education and information for patients and carers, is an important element. The post holder is expected to work in partnership with the multi-disciplinary teams and will have close working relationship with urology consultants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will act as a resource to health care professionals, both internal and external.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please contact Jan Golding, Urology-Oncology Nurse Practitioner on 01284 7122806 or email &lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;j&lt;/span&gt;an&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;ice.golding@wsh.nhs.uk&lt;/span&gt;. Informal visits would be welcomed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;**In order to improve efficiency, all correspondence relating to this vacancy, &lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;including invitations to interview will be by email only&lt;/span&gt;, via NHS Jobs. Would you therefore please ensure you check your emails on a regular basis**&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In submitting an application form, you authorise West Suffolk NHS FT to confirm any previous NHS service details via the Inter Authority Transfer (IAT) process, should you be appointed to the post. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CAR PARKING&lt;/strong&gt; - This post &lt;strong&gt;does&lt;/strong&gt; entitle you to apply to park on the Hospital site.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate for this post will be required to apply for a Disclosure &amp; Barring Service (DBS) Disclosure at Enhanced level.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For Band 1 and Band 2 posts, the cost of the DBS Disclosure will be met by the Trust. However, any employees at Band 1 and Band 2 who leave the Trust within six months of commencing their post will have a £10 administration fee deducted from their final salary. For posts at Band 3 and above, the cost of the Disclosure will be met by the appointed employee and deducted in instalments from their salary over a period of three months. If the employee leaves the Trust within three months of commencing their post, any outstanding payments will be deducted from their final pay.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All applicants should click on the link entitled “How will my application be processed?” prior to submitting their application form.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The closing date for this vacancy may change if we receive a strong response. Please ensure that you apply for any post you are interested in as soon as possible.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
